ReportText: EXAM: XR CHEST 2 VIEWS CXR HISTORY: 4-year-old male, cough, fever, vomiting. Initial encounter. TECHNIQUE: PA and lateral chest radiographs were obtained. COMPARISON: None. FINDINGS: Lungs are clear without confluent airspace opacity, pleural effusion, or pneumothorax. Cardiomediastinal silhouette is normal. Bones are normal. IMPRESSION: Normal radiographic examination of the chest.
